! Variable references

* Simple variable: <<currentTiddler>>
* Built-in: <<now "YYYY-0MM-0DD">>
* In a filter: {{{ [<currentTiddler>] }}}
* As an attribute value: <$text text=<<currentTiddler>>/>

! Text references

Text references address a tiddler field, index or property.

* Field of current tiddler: {{!!title}}
* Field of another tiddler: {{HelloThere!!caption}}
* Index of a data tiddler: {{MyData##key}}
* In a filter operand: {{{ [get{!!modified}] }}}
* As a widget attribute: <$text text={{!!title}}/>

! Multi-valued variables

* Display form: ((myListVariable))
* With a separator: ((myListVariable||, ))
* In a filter: {{{ [(myListVariable)] }}}

! Substituted attribute values (backticks)

Backtick-quoted attribute values allow embedded substitution. This is distinct
from inline code.

* Single backtick: <$text text=`Hello $(currentTiddler)$`/>
* With a filter substitution: <$text text=`There are ${ [tag[done]count[]] }$ done items`/>
* Triple backtick (allows literal backticks):
<$text text=```a literal ` backtick, and $(currentTiddler)$```/>

Within a substituted value:
* `$(varname)$` substitutes a variable's value
* `${ filter }$` substitutes the result of a filter

! Setting variables

<$let
	colour="red"
	size="big"
	greeting=`Hello from $(currentTiddler)$`
>
Inside the let: <<colour>>, <<size>>, <<greeting>>.
</$let>

<$set name="answer" value="42">
The answer is <<answer>>.
</$set>

<$vars name="Jane" role="admin">
<<name>> is an <<role>>.
</$vars>

! Parameters via the parameters widget

<$parameters first="a" second="b">
<<first>> and <<second>>
</$parameters>
